<tr>
<td colspan="3" class="boilerplate metadata" style="line-height:10pt; padding:0.5em;"><small><b>Note</b>: This page may contain <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA" title="Wikipedia:IPA">IPA</a> phonetic symbols in <a href="/wiki/Unicode" title="Unicode">Unicode</a>.</small></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><b>Izi</b> (or <b>Izzi</b>) is an <a href="/wiki/Igboid_languages" title="Igboid languages">Igbo dialect</a> spoken in <a href="/wiki/Ebonyi_State" title="Ebonyi State">Ebonyi state</a> in <a href="/wiki/Nigeria" title="Nigeria">Nigeria</a> by approximately 200,000 people,<sup id="cite_ref-Meier_0-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Meier-0"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> or 600,000 including the closely related to <a href="/wiki/Ikwo" title="Ikwo" class="mw-redirect">Ikwo</a>, <a href="/wiki/Ezza" title="Ezza">Ezza</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Mgbo" title="Mgbo">Mgbo</a>, which form a <a href="/wiki/Dialect_cluster" title="Dialect cluster" class="mw-redirect">dialect cluster</a> known as Izi-Ezaa-Ikwo-Mgbo. This language will be referred to simply as <i>Izi.</i></p>
<table id="toc" class="toc">
